Decisions still source from markdown, not changelog (D-8 preserved) — exporter skips the decisions table.', 'done', 'high', 'claude', NULL, 'D-15', '2026-05-08 07:46:54', '2026-05-08 10:22:35', NULL, 'de16f5e34ce854dd843ce543dc0189e0', 1) ON CONFLICT(id) DO UPDATE SET type=excluded.type, parent_id=excluded.parent_id, title=excluded.title, description=excluded.description, status=excluded.status, priority=excluded.priority, assigned_to=excluded.assigned_to, team=excluded.team, decision_ref=excluded.decision_ref, updated_at=excluded.updated_at, deleted_at=excluded.deleted_at, hash=excluded.hash, canonical_version=excluded.canonical_version WHERE excluded.updated_at > tickets.updated_at OR (excluded.updated_at = tickets.updated_at AND excluded.hash > tickets.hash);
INSERT INTO tickets (id, type, parent_id, title, description, status, priority, assigned_to, team, decision_ref, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at, hash, canonical_version) VALUES ('T-20', 'task', 'T-16', 'rewrite pql plan import to replay changelog directories', 'Replace JSON import with changelog replay. Walk .pql/changelog/<table>/ directories in lexicographic file order so 0000-schema.sql and other zero-prefixed schema files run before year-prefixed data files. Replay every line that hasn''t been seen since last_import_marker (tracked per-file via mtime or per-line via offset).

Import pipeline (internal/cli/plan.go + internal/planning/changelog/importer.go):
1. Read last_import_marker from pql.db meta.
2. For each .pql/changelog/<table>/ directory:
   a. Run files in lexicographic order, tracking position.
   b. Schema files apply via CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS (idempotent).
   c. Data files: each line is an inline-guarded upsert; replay is idempotent because the WHERE clause from T-19 prevents stale lines from overwriting newer state.
3. Advance last_import_marker on success.

Idempotency is load-bearing: the same line replayed N times converges to the same result, regardless of starting state. This is the property that lets the hooks (D-18) be cheap and the import to fire from multiple paths (post-merge, pql plan rebuild) without coordination.

Touches: internal/cli/plan.go (import verb body), new internal/planning/changelog/importer.go, internal/planning/repo/meta.go. Tests: replay-twice convergence, replay-out-of-order convergence, schema_version mismatch handling (refuse and surface diagnostic), partial-replay resumption after interrupted run.', 'done', 'high', 'claude', NULL, 'D-15', '2026-05-08 07:47:06', '2026-05-08 10:41:27', NULL, '5ed648a627e9b273a6541ff3fb573700', 1) ON CONFLICT(id) DO UPDATE SET type=excluded.type, parent_id=excluded.parent_id, title=excluded.title, description=excluded.description, status=excluded.status, priority=excluded.priority, assigned_to=excluded.assigned_to, team=excluded.team, decision_ref=excluded.decision_ref, updated_at=excluded.updated_at, deleted_at=excluded.deleted_at, hash=excluded.hash, canonical_version=excluded.canonical_version WHERE excluded.updated_at > tickets.updated_at OR (excluded.updated_at = tickets.updated_at AND excluded.hash > tickets.hash);
INSERT INTO tickets (id, type, parent_id, title, description, status, priority, assigned_to, team, decision_ref, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at, hash, canonical_version) VALUES ('T-21', 'task', 'T-16', 'implement pql plan rebuild for branch-switch and rebase recovery', 'New subcommand pql plan rebuild — drops planning tables and replays the full changelog from scratch. Used by post-checkout (branch switch) and post-rewrite (rebase) hooks because LWW-guarded incremental replay can only INSERT/UPDATE — it can''t remove rows that exist on the previous branch but not the new one.

Rebuild pipeline (internal/cli/plan.go):
1. DELETE FROM each planning table (or DROP and rely on schema files to recreate — simpler).
2. Reset last_import_marker, last_export_marker.
3. Run the import flow from T-20 against the entire changelog.
4. Stdout: summary (tables rebuilt, rows replayed, time taken).
5. Stderr: progress diagnostics for hook visibility.

Surface as a first-class command, not just a hook callee — power users may invoke it for disaster recovery or after manual changelog edits. Document under ''Plan subcommands'' in the skill.

Touches: internal/cli/plan.go (new rebuild verb), reuses the importer from T-20. Tests: rebuild-from-empty, rebuild-after-branch-with-deleted-rows (must not leak previous branch state), idempotent re-rebuild.', 'done', 'high', 'claude', NULL, 'D-18', '2026-05-08 07:47:16', '2026-05-08 10:44:10', NULL, 'ca2e67fa614bbb4d534f2fde30586c78', 1) ON CONFLICT(id) DO UPDATE SET type=excluded.type, parent_id=excluded.parent_id, title=excluded.title, description=excluded.description, status=excluded.status, priority=excluded.priority, assigned_to=excluded.assigned_to, team=excluded.team, decision_ref=excluded.decision_ref, updated_at=excluded.updated_at, deleted_at=excluded.deleted_at, hash=excluded.hash, canonical_version=excluded.canonical_version WHERE excluded.updated_at > tickets.updated_at OR (excluded.updated_at = tickets.updated_at AND excluded.hash > tickets.hash);
INSERT INTO tickets (id, type, parent_id, title, description, status, priority, assigned_to, team, decision_ref, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at, hash, canonical_version) VALUES ('T-6', 'bug', NULL, 'pql init writes hooks to .git/hooks/ even when core.hooksPath is redirected', 'When git''s core.hooksPath config points at a custom directory (this repo uses ''.githooks/'' for its pre-push gate), git ignores .git/hooks/ entirely — so the pql shim ensureGitHookShim writes there is never invoked, and the .pql/hooks/{pre-commit,post-merge} scripts never fire from git commit / git pull. Witnessed locally: the show-tree unification commit (T-2) didn''t auto-stage .pql/pql-plan.json even though pql plan export --stage works correctly when run by hand.

Reproducer: ''git config core.hooksPath .githooks'' in any pql-init''d repo. Commits stop carrying the snapshot.

Fix: ensureGitHookShim in internal/cli/init.go should resolve the effective hooks path. Two strategies:
  1. Read ''git config --get core.hooksPath'' (or the equivalent env var GIT_HOOKS_PATH) and write the shim there. If the directory doesn''t exist or isn''t writable, surface a clear note in the init JSON output rather than silently planting a dead shim.
  2. Append to an existing pre-commit/post-merge shim in that directory rather than overwriting (so the project''s own hook keeps working alongside pql''s).

Test: assert ensurePlanExportHook with a pre-set core.hooksPath writes into the redirected dir, not .git/hooks/.', 'done', 'high', 'claude', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-06 12:08:36', '2026-05-08 10:55:14', NULL, '04b346775c894465f5d9653c84f2b0ec', 1) ON CONFLICT(id) DO UPDATE SET type=excluded.type, parent_id=excluded.parent_id, title=excluded.title, description=excluded.description, status=excluded.status, priority=excluded.priority, assigned_to=excluded.assigned_to, team=excluded.team, decision_ref=excluded.decision_ref, updated_at=excluded.updated_at, deleted_at=excluded.deleted_at, hash=excluded.hash, canonical_version=excluded.canonical_version WHERE excluded.updated_at > tickets.updated_at OR (excluded.updated_at = tickets.updated_at AND excluded.hash > tickets.hash);
INSERT INTO tickets (id, type, parent_id, title, description, status, priority, assigned_to, team, decision_ref, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at, hash, canonical_version) VALUES ('T-5', 'task', NULL, 'harden plan export hook: --stage flag + absolute pql path', 'Two related issues with the pre-commit hook installed by pql init:

1. Staging logic lives in shell, not pql. Move it into ''pql plan export --stage'' so pql owns the git-add edge cases (untracked / gitignored / dirty). Bare ''pql plan export'' stays side-effect-free; --stage opts in. Update internal/cli/init.go''s pqlPreCommitHook to call ''pql plan export --stage'' (one line, no [ -f ] test).

2. Hook silently no-ops when pql isn''t on PATH for git''s hook shell (witnessed locally — git commit -m ''...'' didn''t fire the hook even though pql was on the user''s interactive PATH). Fix: at pql init time, resolve os.Executable() and bake the absolute path into the generated hook script instead of ''pql''. Drop the ''command -v pql'' guard since the absolute path either exists or it doesn''t.

Touches: internal/cli/init.go (hook content), internal/cli/plan.go (export verb adds --stage flag and stage helper). Requires a new repo-level helper or direct git shell-out for the staging step. Add tests: hook-content assertion that the resolved path is baked in; cli test for ''plan export --stage'' both when file is untracked and when it''s already tracked.', 'done', 'high', 'claude', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-06 10:14:20', '2026-05-08 10:55:14', NULL, '1d127f528353dbb3cd18f93f2b1a91e1', 1) ON CONFLICT(id) DO UPDATE SET type=excluded.type, parent_id=excluded.parent_id, title=excluded.title, description=excluded.description, status=excluded.status, priority=excluded.priority, assigned_to=excluded.assigned_to, team=excluded.team, decision_ref=excluded.decision_ref, updated_at=excluded.updated_at, deleted_at=excluded.deleted_at, hash=excluded.hash, canonical_version=excluded.canonical_version WHERE excluded.updated_at > tickets.updated_at OR (excluded.updated_at = tickets.updated_at AND excluded.hash > tickets.hash);
INSERT INTO tickets (id, type, parent_id, title, description, status, priority, assigned_to, team, decision_ref, created_at, updated_at, deleted_at, hash, canonical_version) VALUES ('T-3', 'task', 'T-1', 'align decisions show with the join-tree helper pattern', 'Audit internal/cli/decisions.go (decisions show with --with-refs / --with-tickets) for a parallel ad-hoc tree shape. If found, factor into a buildDecisionTree helper analogous to buildShowTree so decision rendering stays consistent across decisions show, decisions read, and any future surface (e.g. plan status drilldowns).', 'done', 'medium', 'claude', NULL, NULL, '2026-05-06 10:07:05', '2026-05-08 10:55:14', NULL, '2aa1a461a5d1bcb632857fc3ef045caf', 1) ON CONFLICT(id) DO UPDATE SET type=excluded.type, parent_id=excluded.parent_id, title=excluded.title, description=excluded.description, status=excluded.status, priority=excluded.priority, assigned_to=excluded.assigned_to, team=excluded.team, decision_ref=excluded.decision_ref, updated_at=excluded.updated_at, deleted_at=excluded.deleted_at, hash=excluded.hash, canonical_version=excluded.canonical_version WHERE excluded.updated_at > tickets.updated_at OR (excluded.updated_at = tickets.updated_at AND excluded.hash > tickets.hash);
